snippet: After inspiring many of its neighbors at the onset of the Arab Spring, it is Tunisia that again could show the way to get the transitions to democracy back on track.
abstract: Editorial welcomes agreement reached between Tunisia's ruling Islamists and opposition parties to put a caretaker administration in charge until new elections can be held; expresses hope that Tunisians can show other Arab countries that political compromise is possible.
lead_paragraph: After inspiring many of its neighbors at the onset of the Arab Spring, it is Tunisia that again could show the way to get the transitions to democracy back on track.
